CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 14, 1958, pg. A11 reads: "Dimpled Debs And Escorts - Among the 17 debs who bowed at the AKA Cotillion Saturday night were, seated: Johnnie Mae Jackson and Madeline Roberson. Standing, left to right, debs and escorts: Janet Bell, Colton Peek, Gloria Hall, Wendell Smith, Signora Hall, Ronald Williams and Delores Murphy."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated: Johnnie Mae Jackson and Madeline Roberson; standing, from left: Janet Bell, Colton Peek, Gloria Hall, Wendell Smith, Signora Hall, Ronald Williams, and Delores Murphy, posed for Alpha Kappa Alpha's seventh debutante cotillion
